article.headline: LSU holds on for 84-76 win over Louisiana-Lafayette in NIT

images.name: Tigers' Sampson shows off with dunk
images.caption: Brandon Sampson drives then throws down the hard tomahawk jam.

article.linkText: LSU holds on for 84-76 win over Louisiana-Lafayette in NIT
article.story: LAFAYETTE, La. -- — Cedric Russell scored 19 points as Louisiana-Lafayette defeated LSU-Alexandria 90-75 on Tuesday night. Devin Butts added 18 points, and Dou Gueye and Mylik Wilson each had 15 for the Ragin' Cajuns (3-1). Gueye also had 17 rebounds, while Wilson posted seven rebounds and six assists. Jalen Perkins had 16 points for the Generals. Jakemin Abney added 12 points, and Joe Lewis had 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
